-- int_deduped_channels.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate customer channels to primary attribution (earliest per customer)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        attributed_at,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY customer_id
            ORDER BY attributed_at ASC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_customer_channels') }}
)
SELECT
    customer_id,
    channel
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- fct_revenue_by_channel.sql
```sql
-- Calculate customer revenue and metrics by attribution channel and store city
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        transaction_id,
        customer_id,
        store_id,
        amount
    FROM {{ ref('stg_transactions') }}
)
SELECT
    COALESCE(ch.channel, '(unknown)') AS channel,
    COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)') AS city,
    SUM(t.amount) AS total_revenue,
    COUNT(t.transaction_id) AS transaction_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT t.customer_id) AS unique_customers
FROM source t
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_stores') }} s
    ON s.store_id = t.store_id
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_channels') }} ch
    ON ch.customer_id = t.customer_id
GROUP BY
    COALESCE(ch.channel, '(unknown)'),
    COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)')
